10-2025

Both scripts:

Supress notificaion display of warnings from the Zenity process itself.
----------------------------------------------------------------------
gksudo2

Remove ROOT_FM variable only used/imported from the optional filemanager-gksudo2 script.
Handle user options -u(user) --user(user), when there are no spaces between -u/--user and the username. This prevents inadvertently running as the root user, instead of the intended user.
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
gksudo-su

Suppress a few more warnings, but allow more warnings to be printed if the pkexec call fails.  In particular this allows the user to see the admonition from Gnome/Nautilus that root access is not allowed.
